My first day ride report http://42bikes.warnock.me.uk/2012/06/18/lejog-day-01/

MORE JOBS FOR MUSICIANS! My ordinance to reform a local law to allow acoustic musicians to perform on outdoor patios PASSED UNANIMOUSLY today in City Council committee! The old law banned acoustic musicians on street-level restaurant patios. The new law will allow one acoustic musician to enhance outdoor dining in Minneapolis!
Group from Shiloh Methodist Church in Cincinnati made it here and is already working hard!

Red-letter day yesterday: the girls made breakfast while Paul and I slept in!  When they called us to come to the table it was wiped off and set with condiments, silverware and plates loaded with pancakes, gallo pinto and macaroni and cheese...all of which they had taken out of the fridge and heated up on the gas stove! They are 6 and 4! I trust that if they'd started a fire or burned themselves they would have woken us up. But since they didn't, maybe they will make this a Sunday tradition...
It's Bad Analogy Monday!
